{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769534433,"nonce":"Vjn/EX+gxPe4pvErk/UjrfLXw0M=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mK71E","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/69","origin":"github"},"title":"Make sure it's easy to discover that an agent started work on an issue","message":"When an agent tackles an issue, an initial plan should be written and commited to a branch and submitted as a draft PR while the work is done. This plan should be updated, commited, and pushed as necessary. It could live in an .agent/scratchpad dir in the target repositorie's root directory.\n\nThe implementor should consider if this is the best idea or if there is a better alternative to have a quicker idea of which issues are being worked on while browsing github.\n\nThe idea of commiting and updating a plan is to allow other agents to take over if necesasry.","files":null}]}